CENTURION, South Africa (AP) — South Africa captain Temba Bavuma won the toss and chose to bat Tuesday in the first cricket test against West Indies.Bavuma is taking charge after replacing Dean Elgar as skipper in a surprise move just before the two-test series. Elgar will continue to play for the team.South Africa fielded a new-look lineup at the start of a new era under Bavuma and new coach Shukri Conrad.Top-order batter Tony de Zorzi and fast bowler Gerald Coetzee were selected for their debuts and allrounder Senuran Muthusamy was recalled for his third test and first since 2019, replacing regular spinner Keshav Maharaj.West Indies kept 34-year-old fast bowler Shannon Gabriel in the team after he made his return in a series win in Zimbabwe this month. He’s part of a pace attack that also includes Jason Holder, Kemar Roach and Alzarri Joseph.Left-arm spinner Gudakesh Motie, who starred in the win in Zimbabwe, is out with injury.ADVERTISEMENT ___Lineups:South Africa: Dean Elgar, Aiden Markram, Tony de Zorzi, Temba Bavuma (captain), Keegan Petersen, Heinrich Klaasen, Senuran Muthusamy, Marco Jansen, Kagiso Rabada, Anrich Nortje, Gerald Coetzee. West Indies: Kraigg Brathwaite (captain), Tagenarine Chanderpaul, Raymon Reifer, Jermaine Blackwood, Kyle Mayers, Roston Chase, Joshua Da Silva, Jason Holder, Alzarri Joseph, Kemar Roach, Shannon Gabriel.___ More AP cricket: https://apnews.com/hub/cricket and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports